1:1 COMMENT "# string_split.z -- Phase S3 splitting via iterators."
1:54 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `sv.split` returns a splitter class. Each iteration of a `for`"
3:65 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# loop yields one substring view; the view is released at end of"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# body before the next fragment materialises (single exclusive"
5:63 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# view on the source at any time)."
6:35 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#"
7:2 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# `sv.split_once` returns the byte index of the first separator,"
8:65 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# or `none`. Callers slice the view themselves."
9:48 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#"
10:2 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# `sv.lines` iterates lines split on '\\n', stripping a paired"
11:62 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# '\\r\\n' for Windows endings."
12:30 EOL "\n"
13:1 EOL "\n"
